  "prompt": "What is the Golden Gate bridge named after?",
  "response": "The Golden Gate Bridge is named after the Golden Gate Strait, the entrance to the San Francisco Bay from the Pacific Ocean. The strait itself was named by Captain John C. Fr\u00e9mont in 1846, who reportedly thought the entrance resembled a \"golden gate\" because it reminded him of the Golden Horn in Istanbul, Turkey. The name predates the famous California Gold Rush of the late 1840s. The bridge, completed in 1937, spans this strait and has since become an iconic symbol of San Francisco and the broader United States.",
